HEADWORD: Concentrativeness
<hw>Con*cen"tra*tive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality of concentrating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>The faculty or propensity which
has to do with concentrating the intellectual the intellectual
powers.</def> <rj><au>Combe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concentrator</ent>⟦br⟧
